<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<para>&krayon; is a full featured image manipulation program. You can
use &krayon; for all your image creation and editing needs, such as
making web images, touching up scanned photographs, creating original
art, or anything else you might need to do with bitmapped images.</para>

<para>What makes &krayon; different, and special, is ease of use
compared with other high-end applications, and full integration with
&koffice; and &kde;. Because of this, &krayon; supports drag and drop,
themes, embedding, and many other advanced features you expect from a
modern desktop environment. Ease of use is important to amateur users,
but even more important to professional artists who must spend many
hours a day using such applications to work with images.</para>

<para>&krayon; is primarily a painting program with some image
processing capabilities. More capabilities can be added with
plugins. Using native and foreign plugins, and parts which can reuse
other &kde; components, additional tools and utilities can be added as
needed.</para>

<para>&krayon; uses &XML; as its native file format. This allows import
filters for almost every type of image file format to be easily
created. It also allows other programs to more easily import &krayon;
files.</para>

</chapter>

