<appendix id="installation">
<title>Installation</title>

<para>&krayon; is included as part of the &koffice; package of
&kde;. Source code or prebuilt binary distributions of the &koffice;
package can be found at the main &kde; &FTP; site, <ulink
url="ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/">ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/</ulink>, or
from one of many mirror sites. A current list of mirror sites can be
found at <ulink url="http://www.kde.org/mirrors.html">
http://www.kde.org/mirrors.html</ulink>.</para>

<para>In order to install and use &krayon; you must have:</para>

<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>A functioning &UNIX; or &UNIX; like system with the X Windowing
System configured.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>The K Desktop Environment 2.x (KDE 2.x). You will need at
least the &Qt; 2.2.3 &GUI; toolkit, the kdesupport, the kdelibs, and
the kdebase packages. Information on obtaining and installing &kde;
2.x can be found at: <ulink
url="http://www.kde.org/">http://www.kde.org/</ulink>.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Permission to install software on your computer. If you are
on a stand alone system, this will not be a problem. If you are
using a networked computer, check with your administrator.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>

<para>Instructions for installing &koffice; from either a source code or
binary package can be found at <ulink
url="http://www.koffice.org/">http://www.koffice.org/</ulink>.</para>

</appendix>

